{"name":"Shadow Trickery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"An assassin with this edge can use the shadows to provide them advantages and opportunities to escape, close, or strike.</p><p>The assassin can take one of the following actions by making a Stealth check with a –1 penalty. Range of any effect is character’s Spirit die.</p><p>• Douse a single light source, no larger than a lantern or lamp. The light source re-illuminates at the end of the assassin’s next turn. </p><p>• Create a distracting movement in the shadows causing a single target to become Distracted. With a raise on the Stealth roll, a second target is Distracted as well. </p><p>• Cause shadows to cling and pull at an enemy giving a –1 penalty to Pace and any actions taken until the end of the target’s next turn. </p><p>• Become obscured as if the illumination was one step lower (Dim to Dark, Dark to Pitch Darkness) for the rest of the encounter. This effect requires the initial illumination to be at least Dim.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.mSoZJqrwMO0Q5I2q"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tzwiv2cvamb","path":"Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"0PMvPknbXxiwSL86"}
