{"name":"Stunning Gloom","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The unnatural shadow weapon causes a weakness that can be exploited.</p><p>Any attack made with a shadow blade that causes at least a Shaken effect also makes the target Vulnerable. If you spend a Benny, the target is Stunned instead.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Shadow Blade"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.dwzQurEdr7dYKi9R"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tzwiv2cvamb","path":"Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"1iq3eabn65S74h0O"}
{"name":"Accuracy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Sharp eyes, precises movements, the hero always hits even the smallest target.</p><p>The hero only suffers half of the Called Shot penalties (rounded up), including to Disarm. This applies before any other penalty reduction.</p><p>Also, Called Shots and Disarm can be used with free attacks","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d6+, Notice d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.Q4sF1F3lvPJoiMzS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2XtcHvgkbabxHja6"}
{"_id":"2pY5RrqVl1NEzxfg","name":"Enhance Spirit Weapon","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">The warrior adept is able to improve her Spirit Weapon with two additional Feature slots. Each time this Edge is </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">taken the hero may completely re-imagine their weapon, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">which means all Features and Flaws can be re-allocated or changed. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Enhance Spirit Weapon may only be selected once per </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Rank. If taken at hero creation, this counts as the Novice selection, and this Edge cannot be taken again until the character reaches Seasoned Rank. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Source:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\"> The Warrior Adept, page 2</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Warrior Adept)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.A58IkTqgPRFg3DEh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6htvanvnugv","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Ebb And Flow","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While the hero is under the effects of Liquid Courage, his movements are highly unpredictable.</p><p>His Pace in combat is reduced by 2, but attacks against him are made at –2 (as long as he can reasonably move about and isn’t suffering any Encumbrance or Minimum Strength penalties)","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Liquid Courage"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.LieMtAlbIrj44ANk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"3jjHu1jwpIY4YMBF"}
{"name":"Improved Shadow Blade","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character can now summon two shadow weapons at the same time. Additionally, the damage of the weapon increases to Str+d6, AP 4.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Shadow Blade"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.vGPS5ruIUn8xhzCl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tzwiv2cvamb","path":"Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"4i3pr8vutX2EJOoe"}
{"name":"Calm Before the Storm","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Whether from meditation, taking time to gather energies, or careful repeating the magic words he will have to pronounce, the hero spends time preparing before unleashing fury on his enemies.</p><p> When the hero takes his entire turn focusing his magic (no movement, no Multi-Actions, can’t be Shaken or Stunned), he gets to ignore up to 2 points of penalties (including Multi-Action penalties) on each power he activates on his next turn. If not used on that next turn, the focus is lost.","notes":"Fantasy: Wizards and Mystics page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.0DN9Jbx68nNktVJj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"5r6fFi0AisvxAmwz"}
{"name":"Living Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This natural caster is able to benefit from Power Edges and Modifications without the use of a wand. Even for him, it is not an easy task. Whenever he uses a Modifier or the Wizard, Artificer or Healer Edge (provided he has them) without a wand, he suffers a –1 penalty to his Wandslinging roll.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.ht4KdsVO0m1aoeNw"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jkt1rsb4ya","path":"Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"6ESK96x32tXUYuMM"}
{"name":"Tattoo Companion","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A special tattoo, infused with shadow, covers a part of this hero. The tattoo shows a creature similar to an animal. The shadows seem to swirl as if alive.</p><p>The exact companion is chosen from the options below when the hero gains this Edge and cannot be changed once choosen. The shadow creature can be called at any time and will appear at the hero’s side as a free action once per hour. It may return to the tattoo as a free action whenever adjacent to the hero. If the companion is Incapacitated, it automatically returns to the tattoo, and must remain there for at least a week.</p><p>When called from the tattoo, the creature looks almost normal, but more sinister, otherworldly, or slightly off. It often inspires fear or revulsion among the common folk. Each companion receives the following special ability: </p><p>• Shared Mind: It can communicate with the tattooed hero as if using mind link.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Vigor d6+, Occult d8+ or Shadowcraft d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.RU4mw0XVC69AXTiz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tzwiv2cvamb","path":"Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"8Ip9t3FNU8QUHAEF"}
