{"name":"Challenging Cry","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The first time each round the hero Wounds or Incapacitates an enemy with an attack or power, he gets a free Intimidation or Taunt Test targeting (at least) that enemy or another enemy (of his choice) who saw his comrade take the blow","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Intimidation d8+ or Taunt d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.pkoxV8ASD4rMlDn5"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"BCi9KKs3DOkFUMyI"}
{"name":"Companion","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Whether he has great charisma, a magic attunement of some sort, received a family heritage or built it himself, your character is strongly tied to a Companion.<p>The Companion and your character are both Loyal (like the Hindrance) to each other. While they are close and usually work together, the Companion can have its own goal and agenda. It gladly helps its master whenever it can, but also follows its instinct, especially when survival is at stake.<p>Create a Companion (see Making Companions, page 8). The Companion does not talk or talks in a language nobody can understand. It doesn’t understand its master or other people either. If the Companion dies, it will come back or be replaced within a few days or weeks.<p>In addition to the Companion, choose one Companion Boons, based on the nature of the relationship between the master and its Companion.","notes":"Fantasy: Companions and Familiars page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.6SYricoZcCITo3xW"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CuF1lNtv5vb52M8E"}
{"name":"Explosive Ally","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When one of your hero’s conjured creatures is Incapacitated, it explodes into bony shards, erupts into golden light, or otherwise ends violently as appropriate to its trappings, dealing 2d6 damage to all creatures adjacent to it. This damage can be Evaded.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, summon ally or zombie"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.Em7tKX5LbQsbHCvH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f8iqtb32o77","path":"Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"E5iM35sM4SuN79BZ"}
{"name":"Lapidarist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"An experienced Petramancer can activate inherent powers in gems and crystals. This hero can spend up to three Power Points to activate an associated power from any crystal or gemstone in her possession. This allows her to use any power normally available from that type of stone of her Rank or lower in her particular setting, provided that the power costs less than 3 Power Points (including the cost of any modifiers). </p><p>Drawing out a power takes incredible concentration. While using this ability, the Petramancer can do nothing else for her entire turn but make a Petramancy roll at –2 (no Multi-Actions can be taken that turn). </p><p>The Petramancer uses her personal Power Points to activate the power, and once the power’s initial Duration is finished (it cannot be maintained) the stone goes inert (but can be used again in the future). This is the Gadgeteer edge reimagined for this Arcane Background.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Petramancy), Petramancy d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.QiGuw84dpeW13CAK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n9geqn0bl2k","path":"Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EU6wTnQrMmRwYHM8"}
{"name":"Shadow Veil","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some assassins become so intimately familiar with shadows, they begin to rely on their aid any time they practice their trade. These shadowy assassins learn to deal devastating damage to their targets if they remain patient and let the shadows slowly find and exploit the target’s weak spots. </p><p>To use this ability both the attacker and the target must be in an area of Dim or darker illumination and a maximum of the assassin’s Spirit die in inches apart. The assassin can place a veil of shadow on a target once each turn as an action (applying the usual Multi-Action penalty). They may continue to place further layers of the veil, one for each Rank they possess. When they decide to strike, they can add +1 bonus to the damage of a successful attack for each layer placed, as long as the target hasn’t moved outside of Spirit reach and the illumination level hasn’t improved above Dim.","notes":"Shadowcraft page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+, Assassin"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.shadowcraft.efDQLFPtHLMF3Blo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tzwiv2cvamb","path":"Shadowcraft","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FLdtbd8sDSe1fnhm"}
{"name":"Arcane Warrior Adept","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The mage is comfortable in armor, and can weave her magic despite the restrictions of metal rings and bindings. She ignores 3 points of Arcane Fatigue from metal armor.","notes":"Dungeon Delvers Toolkit page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic), Strength d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.dungeon-delver.VPSmKadMlPjZkRLT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_pxhks5ssqra","path":"Dungeon Delver","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FYEvcOOPutsQSwYA"}
{"name":"Cavalryman","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While riding, the hero ignores up to two points of penalties to any Riding roll and may spend Bennies to Soak damage for their mount using her Riding skill instead of the mount’s Vigor. Each success and raise negates a Wound.</p><p>Also, if the hero has the Block, Dodge, or Extraction Edges (and improved versions), they also affect the mount she is riding. And with the Counterattack Edge, she can riposte failed attacks against her mount","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 34","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Riding d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.zq1wR26HQZaqj2iZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JdZlmSlX1CyPICni"}
{"name":"Wandslinger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Wandslingers deal instant punishment for an opponent’s mistakes. Once per round (if not Shaken or Stunned), the character receives a Free Attack against one failed arcane skill roll against him. This takes place immediately and must be a Wandslinging attack without Modifiers, using one of the following powers (provided he has them and the opponent is in Range): <i>blind, bolt, dispel, entangle,</i> or <i>slumber</i>. The Power Point cost is applied as a penalty to the Wandslinging roll.<p>These mages also ignore the penalty to disarming with Wandslinging skill and the penalty to Strength when resisting such an attempt (see page 3).","notes":"Wand Magic page 5","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d10"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.hzoX42h0P8XdkUBr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jkt1rsb4ya","path":"Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Jdg0YrHm4qdoZeMO"}
{"name":"Trapstone","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Crystals and gemstones are able to hold onto magical energy for extended periods of time. Some Petramancers can use this unique property to \"pre-load\" stones to trigger powers by adding unique Power Modifiers to their Arcane Devices. All Power Points (including Modifiers) are held in the device until released, making them unavailable to the creator (unless and Artisan Device, see blow). </p><p>• Trigger (+2, Instant Powers Only): Anyone, other than the creator, who touches the gem activates the power using the creator’s Petramancy skill! If the roll fails, only 1 Power Point is spent. The device must have sufficient Power Points to activate the embedded power (including the modifier). This occurs on each subsequent touch until the Power Points are exhausted. </p><p>• Proximity Trigger (+4, Instant Powers Only): Anyone, other than the creator, who passes within a Small Burst Template (Medium Template on a Raise) activates the power using the creator’s Petramancy skill! If the roll fails, only 1 Power Point is spent. The device must have sufficient Power Points to activate the power (including the modifier). This occurs on each subsequent pass until the Power Points are exhausted.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.1Yrz9EgBZZ7000ix"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n9geqn0bl2k","path":"Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KGI33osvwu9y0V3C"}
{"name":"Hit And Run","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero knows how to keep a steady aim despite moving.</p><p>He always ignores the penalty for Running on all of his actions.</p><p>And, once during a turn in which he moves and fires, he can reroll one Shooting or Athletics (throwing) roll","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Steady Hands, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.SA6TFEwcq8TT8Ghr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"M0OXtea9JFBWcHJx"}
{"name":"Multifaceted","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero can combine trappings from two types of gems that have access to the same power to create a unique magical effect by inserting them in the same object (e.g. Ruby and Sapphire might be combined to create \"Blue Flame\" ). Multifaceted powers add +2 to damage and are –1 to resist in addition to gaining any Synergies related to either trapping - including Weaknesses.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Petramancy), Petramancy d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.3xkUBACrkikdOw9h"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n9geqn0bl2k","path":"Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"M4uR7sVkUKVUSPiQ"}
{"name":"Elementalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Each elementalist chooses his favorite element, e.g. fire, ice, or lightning. Powers with this Trapping function as having Limitation (Element). They cost one less Power Point to cast.<p>Furthermore, the Elementalist with Living Wand does not suffer the Wandslinging penalty for powers with Trapping of his chosen element.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, AB (Wand Magic), Wandslinging d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.y1GbiLufv51cHks0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jkt1rsb4ya","path":"Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"N0636HLJcf6neOIP"}
{"name":"Power Trap","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero has learned to create magical triggers that activate a power when another creature moves through an area, reads a magical rune, or otherwise triggers the trap. Common triggers are movement, creature type, anyone who doesn’t say a passphrase, anyone not wearing a certain symbol, or other clear circumstances based on sensory information. When the trap is triggered, it casts a Power that your hero knows against the triggering creature or centered on itself, rolling the caster’s arcane skill as normal. All the choices for this Power are set when the trap is created, and any Power Points are spent. The caster doesn’t get these Power Points back until the trap is either triggered or deactivated. Power traps can be disarmed using the caster’s arcane skill opposed by the disarmer’s Occult or Thievery skill (whichever is worse) with a penalty equal to the Rank of the Power; the trap’s creator can do this automatically.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Occult d8+, Spellcasting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.OdZrswdWzK6mAHXg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f8iqtb32o77","path":"Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"N5qiQNrN5WHqor8O"}
{"name":"Charge","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When the hero charges an enemy by Running, jumping, or riding at least 2” in a straight line to attack them in melee, he gets a free reroll on the damage roll.</p><p>If the attack provides multiple damage rolls, e.g.</p><p>Frenzy or Sweep, choose only one to reroll.</p><p>Any target (no more than two Sizes larger than the hero) hit by this attack must roll Athletics higher than or equal to the damage or fall Prone (mounted enemies fall from their mount)","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d6+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.yDLIH85MtjofQQsB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"N7YINhbwIm9XCuNn"}
{"name":"Bull Rush","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero jostles his enemies harshly: “What stands up must come down” as he likes to say.</p><p>Once per round, the fighter can make a Push or Trip maneuver (see page 40) against two targets adjacent to each other. Each defender resists and is affected by the maneuver separately","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.vskzwDNzIyMQQAQH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NY9o1gNiUZLZqDrc"}
{"name":"Flexible Summoner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is familiar with a number of creatures they can summon, or their summoned spirits are unusually malleable. Instead of one ally choice per Rank, select two different allies of each Rank; your hero can choose between these with each casting of summon ally. She can also spend eight hours of work or meditation to change one of these allies out for another of the same Rank.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Smarts d8+, Occult d8+, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.mLAlTzpVvuaI3eMN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f8iqtb32o77","path":"Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"OnktPAiL5nLU4hPV"}
{"name":"Master Summoner","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero’s custom summoned allies gain an additional number of build points (from Chapter 4, Making a Friend) to allocate equal to your Rank (1 for Novice, 2 for Seasoned, and so on). If you are using an ally from the core rules or from this document, you can select additional enhancements for each of your hero’s allies from that chapter when you gain this Edge, or whenever they learn a new ally. These points can be re‐allocated each time your hero gains a Rank.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Spirit d8+, Occult d8+, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.tucinmEsyuEaxKTK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f8iqtb32o77","path":"Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Pmyc4PES3j8dPU80"}
{"name":"Arcane Artisan","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once per session, an experienced Petramancer can create a jewel-adorned item with an embedded power, which he can give to someone else to use. To create the device, follow the rules for Artificer, with one significant change: unlike other Arcane Devices, items created by an Arcane Artisan do not tie up the creator’s Power Points after creation due to the mystical ability of gems and crystals to store Power Points. Such devices are very expensive and time consuming to create, however. Double the normal Arcane Device creation time. </p><p>Crafting also requires the creator to invest 5 Power Points for each Power Point that will be retained in the stone. Power Points can only be used to activate the power stored in the item and can only be replenished by a Petramancer or by leaving the device to charge in its associated element for at least one hour. </p><p>The item must be made with a stone appropriate to the power being imbued. Power Modifiers and Limitations can be added at creation but are always included in every activation. Activation works the same as other Arcane Devices. These items can also be Trapstones.","notes":"Petramancy page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Petramancer, Artificer, Repair d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.petramancy.gTVQTUVlQxp8jE7a"},"cf":{"id":"temp_n9geqn0bl2k","path":"Petramancy","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QDuO48sKzm3wgzql"}
{"name":"Drunkard’s Luck","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When the hero is under the effects of Liquid Courage in combat, he gains a Benny. If not used, that Benny is lost at the end of the combat","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 32","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Liquid Courage, Luck"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.kKgZooTWyTxDjPSV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QZ4OzveRDUhtS3VZ"}
{"name":"Focus Fire","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Marksman Edge affects all of the shooter’s ranged attacks on his turn, as long as she fires no more than a Rate of Fire of 1, doesn’t move, and targets the same foe.</p><p>Also, when the hero successfully hits a target for the second time in the turn, the target immediately becomes Vulnerable","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Marksman, Athletics d10+ or Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.30yehP5x3JSeYBGR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QZ6rPlGFStMHrk8o"}
{"name":"Brutality","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The hero uses the weight and inertia of his weapon to great effect.</p><p>When wielding a melee weapon with two hands, the hero increases its damage die one type (Str+d10 becomes Str+d12).</p><p>In addition, on a raise, before damage is rolled, he may choose to either push the target 1” away, or have them fall Prone, or deal an additional +2 damage to them. This also applies to free attacks","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 28","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.YdQIWD5eaaNkInK4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"T4wWLZRGab5TszAk"}
{"name":"Dirty Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Honor and rules do not matter when your life is at stake.</p><p>The hero gets +2 to Test an enemy when their next action this turn (taking Multi-Actions) is to attack that same enemy","notes":"Fantasy: Fighters and Warlords page 29","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.lYTQUdEesMkTcCd7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"UVIOzrDPQR9qiqd2"}
{"name":"Rune Wand","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This mage has discovered secret knowledge that allows him to carve a power rune into his wand (and he does so every time he attunes a new wand). He picks a non-damaging power he knows. As long as he is wielding the rune wand, the mage may cast the power with Range reduced to Self as a free action once per turn. The Selective Modifier may not be applied. The wielder spends Power Points as usual.","notes":"Wand Magic page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, AB (Wand Magic)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.wand-magic.HC4Dp3tDgNnwo0xG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jkt1rsb4ya","path":"Wand Magic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"VivCDop41isS3Gvw"}
{"name":"Improved Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Once an artificer has mastered imbuing powers into arcane devices, she can advance to crafting permanent magic items with the Improved Artificer Edge. Artificers with this Edge have the ability to make minor artifacts– items imbued with powers that can recharge their given Power Points.<p>Minor artifacts are particularly useful for equipping characters without the Artificer Edge, since unlike arcane devices, these items can replenish Power Points without the need for an artificer to tinker with it.","notes":"Artificer's Codex page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"V, Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.artificers-codex.WuVA4HdITXo2jRml"},"cf":{"id":"temp_des0e1o1s4h","path":"Artificer's Codex","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"X55i6cJDaHExuK2T"}
{"name":"Battle Mage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The battle mage has seen many fights and learned to defend himself.</p><p> Once during his turn, he may activate a power on himself as a free action. He must be the only target of that power (no Additional Recipient or Area of Effect).","notes":"Fantasy: Wizards and Mystics page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any), Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.fantasy-add-ons.TFLomgEwtvHIMRXO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w7pvxs6rik","path":"Fantasy Add-Ons","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Y82cHWb1Wl0Xo1Gh"}
