{"name":"Master Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who take their study of crafting artifacts to the highest level are able to make major artifacts–permanent magic items that are infused with one or more powers and are continuously active or usable. For example, a wielder holding a major artifact with <i>havoc</i> imbued on it can blast enemies away repeatedly at-will.","notes":"Artificer's Codex page 1","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"H, Improved Artificer"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.artificers-codex.iGCJgfmLNWUfCYee"},"cf":{"id":"temp_des0e1o1s4h","path":"Artificer's Codex","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"abYbyvdN8F7nNmI4"}
{"name":"Crowd Caller","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Sometimes what you really need is numbers on your side, and your character is able to provide. He can summon multiple identical creatures with a single casting of summon ally. This costs an additional two Power Points per additional ally, plus one for every rank of the servant beyond Novice. Each additional ally also increases the cost to maintain the Power by one.","notes":"Summoners Circle page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, summon ally"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.summoners-circle.hd36UY7qFGcZ6DIg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f8iqtb32o77","path":"Summoner's Circle","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bKJn0fScNHmYyXja"}
{"_id":"cdHrjY8hFgkRqayh","name":"Arcane Background (Warrior Adept)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Arcane Skill: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Focus (Spirit) </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Starting Powers: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">2<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Power Points: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">10<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Powers Available: </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Boost/lower </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;\">Trait, damage field, darksight, deflection, farsight, fear, havoc, healing, intangibility, invisibility, protection, relief, sloth/speed, smite, warrior&rsquo;s gift</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Warrior adepts come from all walks of life&mdash; Shaolin monks, street toughs, cage fighters, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">etc. They have access to some powers, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">but their main function is to fight, </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">and so they are the only magic- wielders with access to Spirit Weapons (see below).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Because warrior adepts&rsquo; abilities are internally focused, powers normally usable on others have the Range Limitation of Self, which reduces the Power Point cost for activating those powers (see </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-weight: bold;\">Trappings </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">in </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">). The same Limitation &ldquo;discount&rdquo; should apply to </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">smite</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">, as it can<br />only be cast on the hero&rsquo;s Spirit Weapon. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Havoc </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">and </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">fear </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">are the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">final exceptions&mdash; </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">havoc </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">can only<br />be activated using the Cone Template, emanating from the caster, and </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">fear </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">requires line of sight within the Smarts range listed (these last two do </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">not </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">count as Limitations).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: 16.000000pt; font-family: 'LeagueGothic';\">SPIRIT WEAPON </span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Warrior adepts use their will to form and fight with a </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">weapon made of pure magic. They use their creativity and prowess to create a unique melee weapon, one that can neither be destroyed nor stolen, as long as the warrior adept can breathe life into it. Conjuring the Spirit Weapon is a free action. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">If a Spirit Weapon would ever be considered disarmed, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">taken, sundered (treat Object Toughness as equal to the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">hero&rsquo;s Spirit die type), or in any other way removed from a hero&rsquo;s possession, or rendered useless, it instead dissipates into nothingness for the warrior adept to re- form as a free action on their next turn. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Should a character throw their Spirit Weapon, it will </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">disappear after the attack is resolved. The </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">character can re-form their Spirit Weapon </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">as a free action on their next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Making use of the weapon requires the Fighting skill or Athletics (Throwing) if a </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">thrown weapon. Base range for throwing a Spirit Weapon is 3/6/12. Due to the &ldquo;up close and personal&rdquo; nature of Spirit Weapons, a warrior adept cannot create a weapon which requires </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">Shooting.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">Spirit Weapons can take any </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">form the warrior adept can imagine, and while they typically resemble real world </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">weapons, they don&rsquo;t have to. Mechanically Spirit Weapons start out as a Str+d4 melee weapon, modified with Features and Flaws chosen from the table below. The Spirit Weapon starts with three Feature slots. More Features may be added by applying an equivalent number </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">of Flaws or by taking the Enhance </span><span style=\"font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-size: 10pt;\">Spirit Weapon Edge.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">A Spirit Weapon keeps its </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">current shape, Features, and Flaws whenever formed, unless the </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">warrior adept takes the Enhance </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">Spirit Weapon Edge. Due to their nature, Spirit Weapons are not subject to the Minimum </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">Strength rules (see </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">Savage Worlds</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype;\">).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Example 1: Vern&rsquo;s character is a down home country </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">girl, and she wants to reflect that by making her Spirit </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype'; font-style: italic;\">Weapon a pool cue. She starts with Str+d4 and adds the Two-Handed Flaw, which gives her four slots to work with. Vern decides this pool cue should deal Str+d8 damage (2 slots), provide +1 Parry (1 slot), and have Reach 1 (1 slot). She now has: Pool Cue (Range 3/6/9, Damage Str+d8, Reach 1, +1 Parry). </span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">Example 2: Darrell wants his hero&rsquo;s Spirit Weapon to appear as dual buzz saw shields. He takes Dual Weapon, Parry Increase twice, and Damage Increase once. He needs </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">one slot of Flaws, but the only one that fits is Fighting Only, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">which provides two slots. He chooses Armor Piercing with </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: PalatinoLinotype; font-style: italic;\">his final slot. He now has: Dual Buzz Saw Shield (Damage Str+d6, +2 Parry, Fighting Only)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'PalatinoLinotype';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Features</h2>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Feature</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Slots</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Notes</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Armor Piercing</td>\n<td>Add AP 2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum AP 3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cover</td>\n<td>Provides -2 Cover</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum -4 Cover</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Damage Increase</td>\n<td>Increases damage die type</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Maximum d12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dual Weapon</td>\n<td>Appears as two weapons</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>See Two Weapons and the Two-Fisted Edge in <em>Savage Worlds</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grapple</td>\n<td>Provides +1 bonus when Grappling</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum +4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heavy Weapon</td>\n<td>Counts as a Heavy Weapon</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instant Re-form</td>\n<td>Warrior adept doesn't need to wait for next turn to re-conjure weapon</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lingering Damage</td>\n<td>Continues causing damage after a successful attack</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td>See Lingering Damage Power Modifier in&nbsp;<em>Savage Worlds</em></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Parry Increase</td>\n<td>Provides +1 Parry</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum +3 Parry; is&nbsp;<em>not</em> multiplied by Dual Weapon Feature if Abmidextrous Edge is taken</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reach Increase</td>\n<td>Provides Reach 1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td>Maximum Reach 2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<h2>Flaws</h2>\n<table style=\"width: 98.8806%; height: 148px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Flaw</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 5.84906%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Slots</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Notes</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Fighting Only</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Cannot be thrown</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Reduced Parry</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Weapon has -1 Parry</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;May be taken only once</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Slow Forming</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Takes an Action to conjure</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">Cannot be combined with Instant Re-form Feature</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 13.9623%; height: 33px;\">Two-Handed</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.1321%; height: 33px;\">Must be wielded with two hands</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5.84906%; height: 33px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7358%; height: 33px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"column\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.59C2KcqLOYwH90A2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6htvanvnugv","color":"#000000"}}}
